licious moment the music pierced her private fog, reached her, enveloped her. Everything was fine again, for this was he, Franz, his shy hands, his breath, the soft fuzz on the back of his neck, under her fingernails, and those precious, adorable motions that she had taught him.

“Closer, closer,” she murmured. “Make me feel warm.”

“I’m tired,” he murmured back. “I’m tired to death. Please don’t do what you are doing, please.”

